description: A food delivery system, made in a team of 18 second-year CS students spread across 3 microservices.

description: Small microservices application that simulates the life cycle of a case. N external systems contact a Practice Management System through the use of entity framework core. There is also a microservice dedicated exclusively to authentication and which generates a JWT Bearer token.

description: This project aims to create a backend system for a Discord-like application using microservices architecture. The architecture follows a star topology, where a central service acts as a mediator for communication between other services.

name: URL-shortener
description: The goal of this project is to create a microservice system in Python that allows shortening URLs through a REST API,  storing them in a database, and redirecting to the original addresses. The system uses task queues for asynchronous  processing of URL shortening requests, ensuring high performance and scalability.
